    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Acetylation regulates AMPAR trafficking, turnover and accumulation in neuron\"\n- \" To test whether acetylation affects AMPAR trafficking, we performed AMPAR internalization and insertion assays in cultured hippocampal neurons. We found that SIRT2 inhibition by B2 (20 μM, 24hrs) resulted in a suppression of agonist-induced (AMPA, 100 μM) AMPAR internalization (Beattie et al., 2000) (Figure 4A, n ≥ 15 cells/group, p < 0.05) without affecting glycine (200 μM)-induced receptor insertion (Lu et al., 2001) (Figure 4B, n ≥ 15 cells/group, p > 0.05).\"\n\nFig.5: \"SIRT2 knock-out mice show enhanced AMPAR acetylation and impaired synaptic plasticity\"\n\nFig.6: \"Sirt2-/- mice show impairments in learning and memory\". Experimental description: - \"Primary rat (Sprague Dawley) cortical and hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared as described previously (Wang et al., 2015). \"\n- \"SIRT2 knock-out mice show enhanced ...\"",
